data.chText: （用力）拖，拉，拽
data.enText: to pull sth/sb with a lot of effort

data.chText: 那些货车是马拉的。
data.enText: The wagons were hauled by horses.

data.chText: 他俯身把利兹拉上墙头。
data.enText: He reached down and hauled Liz up onto the wall.

data.chText: 用力缓慢挪动到（某处）
data.enText: to move yourself somewhere slowly and with a lot of effort

data.chText: 她费劲地下了床。
data.enText: She hauled herself out of bed.

data.chText: 强迫（某人）去某处
data.enText: to force sb to go somewhere they do not want to go

data.chText: 一批嫌疑犯被拘捕接受讯问。
data.enText: A number of suspects have been hauled in for questioning.

data.chText: 使某人出庭受审；把某人提交法庭
data.enText: to make sb appear in court in order to be judged

data.chText: 他因危险驾驶而被移交地方法庭审判。
data.enText: He was hauled up before the local magistrates for dangerous driving.
haul sb over the coals
rake sb over the coals

data.chText: 严厉训斥（或斥责）某人
data.enText: to criticize sb severely because they have done sth wrong

data.chText: 大批赃物；大量非法物品
data.enText: a large amount of sth that has been stolen or that is illegal

data.chText: 大批非法武器
data.enText: a haul of weapons

data.chText: 一大批毒品
data.enText: a drugs haul

data.chText: 很高的得分
data.enText: a large number of points, goals, etc.

data.chText: 他在一个赛季中得了40分，创下了纪录。
data.enText: His haul of 40 goals in a season is a record.

data.chText: 旅行的距离；旅程
data.enText: the distance covered in a particular journey

data.chText: 他们踏上了攀登顶峰的漫长行程。
data.enText: They began the long slow haul to the summit.

data.chText: 我们的营地离这里很近。
data.enText: Our camp is only a short haul from here.

data.chText: 走海岸线那条路——这样会好走一些。
data.enText: Take the coast road─it'll be less of a haul (= an easier journey) .

data.chText: 一次捕获的鱼；一网鱼
data.enText: a quantity of fish caught at one time

data.text: pull ♦ drag ♦ draw ♦ haul ♦ tow ♦ tug

data.chText: 以上各词均含拖、拉、拽之意。
data.enText: These words all mean to move sth in a particular direction, especially towards or behind you.
pull

data.chText: 指向某方向拖、拉、牵引：
data.enText: to hold sth and move it in a particular direction; to hold or be attached to a vehicle and move it along behind you

data.chText: 把椅子再往桌子拉近些。
data.enText: Pull the chair nearer the table.

data.chText: 他们用牛拉车。
data.enText: They use oxen to pull their carts.
drag

data.chText: 通常指使劲在地上拖、拉、拽：
data.enText: to pull sb/sth in a particular direction or behind you, usually along the ground, and especially with effort

data.chText: 这麻袋太重了，提不起来。你得拖着走。
data.enText: The sack is too heavy to lift─you'll have to drag it.
draw

data.chText: 指拖动、拉动、牵引、拖车：
data.enText: ( formal ) to move sb/sth by pulling them/it gently; to pull a vehicle such as a carriage

data.chText: 我把椅子向火旁拉近了点。
data.enText: I drew my chair closer to the fire.

data.chText: 马车
data.enText: a horse-drawn carriage
haul

data.chText: 指用力拖、拉、拽：
data.enText: to pull sb/sth to a particular place with a lot of effort

data.chText: 渔民在拉网。
data.enText: Fishermen were hauling in their nets.

data.chText: 用drag还是haul？
drag通常指在身后的地上拖，haul通常指朝面前拉、向上拽。drag常需要用力，而haul总是要用力。
data.enText: You usually drag sth behind you along the ground; you usually haul sth towards you, often upwards towards you. Dragging sth often needs effort, but hauling sth always does.
drag or haul?
tow

data.chText: 指用绳索拖、拉、牵引（汽车、船或轻型飞机）：
data.enText: to pull a car, boat or light plane behind another vehicle, using a rope or chain

data.chText: 我们的汽车被警察拖走了。
data.enText: Our car was towed away by the police.
tug

data.chText: 指朝某一方向用力拖、拉、拽：
data.enText: to pull sb/sth hard in a particular direction

data.chText: 她试图逃跑，但他把她拽了回来。
data.enText: She tried to escape but he tugged her back.
to pull/drag/draw/haul/tow/tug sth back/away/out
to pull/drag/draw/haul/tow/tug sb/sth along/down/towards sth
to pull/drag/draw/haul/tow sb/sth behind you
to pull/draw a coach/carriage/sledge
to pull/haul/tow a truck
to pull/haul a train
horses pull/draw/haul sth
dogs pull/drag/haul sth
engines/locomotives pull/haul sth

ex.chText: 她的小弟弟总是拽她的头发。
ex.enText: Her little brother was always pulling her hair.

ex.chText: 她把儿子轻轻地拉到身边。
ex.enText: She pulled her son gently towards her.

synonyms.bx: 指用手把某物或某人拉向身边或沿着某个方向拉过去。

ex.chText: 她费了很大劲把单人床拖进卧室里。
ex.enText: She managed to drag the single bed to her bedroom.

ex.chText: 那位母亲硬把儿子拽进了幼儿园。
ex.enText: The mother dragged her son into the kindergarten.

synonyms.bx: 指某物因太沉而只能在地面拖着走，也指硬拽某人到其并不想去的地方。

ex.chText: 她把一把椅子拉到壁炉边。
ex.enText: She drew a chair up to the fireplace.
Don't forget to draw the curtains.

ex.chText: 他俯身把同伴拉上墙头。
ex.enText: He reached down and hauled his partner up onto the wall.

ex.chText: 那辆火车是由蒸汽机车拖动的。
ex.enText: The train was hauled by the steam locomotive.

synonyms.bx: 强调一直要用力，方向通常是朝前或向上。

ex.chText: 他的车什么时候被警察拖走的？
ex.enText: When was his car towed away by the police?

ex.chText: 那艘船出了点问题，不得不被拖进港口。
ex.enText: Something was wrong with the ship, and it had to be towed into the harbour.

synonyms.bx: 指用绳索或链条拖拉车或船。

ex.chText: 你认识拽她袖子的男人吗？
ex.enText: Do you know the man who was tugging at her sleeve?

ex.chText: 站在他后面的女人轻轻拽了拽她的胳膊。
ex.enText: The woman standing behind him gently tugged his arm.

synonyms.bx: 强调动作发生的时间短而迅速。

data.enText: haul sb over the coals
rake sb over the coals

data.chText: 严厉训斥（或斥责）某人
data.enText: to criticize sb severely because they have done sth wrong

trans: 使出庭受审；使去见掌权者

tr: the act of drawing or hauling something
example: the haul up the hill went very slowly
haul stones from the quarry in a truck

value.def: If you haul something which is heavy or difficult to move, you move it using a lot of effort.

example.ex: A crane had to be used to haul the car out of the stream...
example.tran: 只好用了起重机，才将轿车从河里拖出来。

example.ex: He hauled himself to his feet...
She hauled up her bedroom window and leaned out.
example.tran: 她拉开卧室的窗户，探出身去。

value.def: If someone is hauled before a court or someone in authority, they are made to appear before them because they are accused of having done something wrong.

example.ex: She was hauled before magistrates for refusing to reveal her age to a policeman...
example.tran: 她因拒绝告诉警察自己的年龄而被地方法院传讯。

example.ex: He was hauled before the managing director and fired.
example.tran: 他被叫去见总裁，然后就被解雇了。

example.ex: He was hauled up before the Board of Trustees...
example.tran: 他被带到了理事会那里。

example.ex: She was late for the interview after being hauled up for speeding.
example.tran: 由于超速驾车被拦下，她面试迟到了。

value.tran: 使出庭受审;使去见掌权者

value.def: A haul is a quantity of things that are stolen, or a quantity of stolen or illegal goods found by police or customs.

example.ex: The size of the drugs haul shows that the international trade in heroin is still flourishing...
example.tran: 本次查获的毒品量表明，海洛因在国际上的交易仍很猖獗。

example.ex: Another break-in yielded a £4,000 haul of jewellery.
example.tran: 另一次入室盗窃偷得了价值4,000英镑的首饰。

value.tran: （警方或海关查获的）一批赃物，一批违禁品

value.def: If you say that a task or a journey is a long haul, you mean that it takes a long time and a lot of effort.

example.ex: Revitalising the Romanian economy will be a long haul.
example.tran: 罗马尼亚经济的复兴将是一项长期而艰巨的工作。

value.tran: 费时费力的事;耗时累人的行程

trans: 短程吊运；短距；短程航线；短距离；短途
使出庭受审；使去见掌权者
